Which, whilst the loss of immunes is sad and all, I dont get why that makes her and the company super duper evil? It also doesn't make too much sense for her to be killing off immunes through too harsh/rushing testing cos there's a limited amount of them, which creates a problem qua finding a cure anyways so... Iuno, I just feel like it's very poorly explained/shown in the movies. You get given more of a "We're telling you she's super duper bad, just trust us aight?".
